phg1explain: DDT to kill mosquitoes sprayed in a fog from the back of a pickup truck. As a child I ran in the fog and inhaled the poison.

Between ages 1 - 12 I spent summers on a family farm.  I remember watching crop dusters spraying what was probably DDT on the fields.  In all probability some of it would have gotten on my skin and I might have breathed in some of it as well.
My brother worked on a farm for most summers in high school. He would spray pesticides and come home smelling like chemicals and with on his clothes. We were exposed that way.

When I was a child, we had a summer home, and once a month the "fog man" would drive around the neighborhood spraying mosquito pesticide from his vehicle; all the neighborhood kids would run behind his truck and play in the fog, because we thought it was cool and fun. I remember it smelled bad and got all over our clothes. I learned later in life that what was sprayed was DDT. My childhood friends and I often reminisce about how stupid and innocent we were to run around and play in DDT.
